        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><rs key="#Boundary_disputes">Lite</rs> mota adversus <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Boundary_disputes #Landed_possessions #Cereals #Forests #Roads #Lakes"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2001">Sancti Benedicti</orgName> a <placeName
                            key="#Urban_communities #Boundary_disputes #Landed_possessions #Cereals #Forests"
                            ref="#places/275">Mantuanis</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Urban_communities">civibus pro commune</rs> de quadam <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs> qua possidebatur a predicto
                        monasterio, partim <rs key="#Cereals">aratoria</rs>, partim <rs
                            key="#Forests">buscalea</rs>, et iacet prope <geogName key="#Villas"
                            ref="#estates/2083"><rs key="#Villas">villam</rs>
                            <placeName key="#Villas #Landed_possessions #Cereals #Forests"
                                ref="#places/2476">Septinenti</placeName></geogName>. Ælecti sunt
                            <rs>viri communi</rs>
                        <rs key="#City_assembly">conscilio</rs>, tam <rs key="#Consules"
                            >consules</rs>, quam <rs key="#Arimannus">arimanni</rs> ad investigandam
                        huius controversie veritatem ipsamque litem finiendam. Cumque domnus
                            <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/3568">Haeinricus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> monasterium per quadraginta annos quiete
                        possedisse, <rs key="#Witness">testibus</rs> probare paratus fuisset eosque
                        cum suis fratribus deprecaretur quatenus monasterium non perturbarent, sed
                        pro remedio animarum suarum quiescere permitterent sicuti antecessores eorum
                        fecere, consules et arimanni communiter cons[ci]lium fecere et timore Dei
                        atque reverentia ipsius monasterii et animarum suarum remedio aliter
                        recesserunt, et finem in manu ipsius abbatis per fustem quem in manibus
                        tenebant per se et toto communi fecerunt. Predicta autem terra de qua finis
                        est, hos fines habet: a mane <rs key="#Roads">via</rs> que pergit ad
                            <placeName key="#Roads">Casalem</placeName> et alia parte vie iuris
                        ipsius monasterii, a meridie <rs key="#Rivers">flumen</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4196">Padi</placeName>, a sera <rs
                            key="#Canals">fossatus</rs>, a septentrione <rs key="#Lakes"
                            >lagullus</rs> qui est iuris Sancti Benedicti. Nomina predictorum
                        consulum et arimannorum sunt haec: <persName
                            key="#Consules #Arimannus #childOf"><name ref="Albertus"
                            >Albertus</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Consules #Arimannus #childOf"><name ref="Azo/f. Azo/Henricus"
                                >Azo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#childOf">filii</rs>
                        <persName key="#parentOf"><name ref="Azo/Heinricus">Azonis
                            Inrici</name></persName>, <persName key="#Consules #Arimannus #childOf"
                                ><name ref="Wido/f. Ugonis/de Bona">Wido</name></persName> filius <persName
                            key="#parentOf"><name ref="Hugo">Ugonis</name></persName> de
                                <persName><name ref="Bona">Bona</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Consules #Arimannus "><name ref="Obizo/de Costantino">Opizo</name></persName> de
                                <persName><name ref="Constantinus">Constantino</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Consules #Arimannus "><name ref="Albertus/de Bonacausa"
                                >Albertus</name></persName> de <persName><name ref="Bonacausa"
                                >Bonacausa</name></persName> de <persName><name ref="Frogerius"
                                >Frogerio</name></persName>; et nomina arimannorum sunt hec:
                            <persName key="#Arimannus"><name ref="Ingelbaldus/de Muciano"
                            >Ingelbaldus</name></persName> de <placeName>Muciano</placeName>,
                            <persName key="#Arimannus #childOf"><name ref="Otto"
                            >Otto</name></persName> et <persName key="#Arimannus #childOf"><name
                                ref="Wibertus">Wibertus</name></persName> atque <persName
                            key="#Arimannus #childOf"><name ref="Anselmus/f. Wiberti"
                            >Anselmus</name></persName> filii eius, <persName key="#Arimannus"><name
                                ref="Albertus/de Azonis">Albertus</name></persName> de Anzoni, <persName
                            key="#Arimannus #childOf #siblingInLawOf"><name ref="Iohannesbonus/de Blanco/de Levada"
                                >Johannes Bonus</name></persName> filius <persName key="#parentOf"
                                ><name ref="Blancus">Blanci</name></persName> de Levada, <persName
                            key="#Arimannus #siblingInLawOf"><name ref="Rodulfus/de Belenthana"
                            >Rodulfus</name></persName> de Belentatha <rs key="#siblingInLawOf"
                            >cognatus</rs> eius, <persName key="#Arimannus"><name
                                ref="Iohannes/Usacurtis">Iohannes Usacurtis</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Arimannus #childOf"><name ref="Albertus/f. Gilberti/de Gudino"
                            >Albertus</name></persName> filius <persName key="#parentOf"
                            >Girberti</persName> de Gudino, <persName key="#Arimannus"
                                ><name ref="Carimannus/Buca de Capra">Carimannus Buca</name></persName> de Capra, <persName
                            key="#Arimannus"><name ref="Turisendus">Turisindus</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Arimannus"><name ref="Obizo">Opizo</name></persName>
                        <rs>nepos</rs>
                        <persName><name ref="Iohannis">Iohannis</name></persName> de <persName><name
                                ref="Obizo">Opizone</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Arimannus #childOf"><name ref="Azo/f. Petri/Pici">Azo</name></persName> filius
                            <persName key="#parentOf"><name ref="Petrus/Pici">Petri
                            Pici</name></persName>, <persName key="#Arimannus"><name ref="Teobaldus/de Puteo"
                                >Teutaldus</name></persName> de Puteo, <persName
                                    key="#Arimannus #childOf"><name ref="Azo/f. Gausi/de Pipo">Azo</name></persName> filius <persName
                            key="#parentOf"><name ref="Gausus/de Pipo">Gausi</name></persName> de Pipo,
                            <persName key="#Arimannus"><name ref="Marchion"
                            >Marchion</name></persName>, <persName key="#Arimannus #childOf"><name
                                ref="Anselmus/f. Litteri">Anselmus</name></persName> filius <persName
                            key="#parentOf"><name ref="Litterius">Literii</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Arimannus"><name ref="Philippus">[Fi]lippus</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Arimannus"><name ref="Sigefredus/de Sancta Agatha"
                            >Sichefredus</name></persName> de Sancta Agatha, <persName
                            key="#Arimannus"><name ref="Albertus/Taliacane">Albertus
                                Taliacane</name></persName>, <persName key="#Arimannus #childOf"
                                    ><name ref="Maginfredus/f. Maginfredi/de Godi">Manfredus</name></persName> et <persName
                                        key="#Arimannus #childOf"><name ref="Albertus/f. Maginfredi/de Godi"
                            >Albertus</name></persName> filii <persName key="#parentOf"><name
                                ref="Maginfredus/de Godi">Manfredi</name></persName> de <placeName ref="#places/2915">Godi</placeName>,
                            <persName key="#Arimannus"><name ref="Hubertus/Malus Denarius">Ubertus
                                Malus Denarius</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Arimannus #childOf"><name ref="Petrus/f. Lanfranci/de Desenzano">Petrus</name></persName>
                        filius <persName key="#parentOf"><name ref="Lanfrancus"
                            >Lanfranci</name></persName> de <placeName ref="#places/4444">Descenzano</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Arimannus #childOf"><name ref="Albertus"
                            >Albertus</name></persName> filius <persName key="#parentOf"><name
                                ref="Peregrinus/de Macia">Pelegrini</name></persName> de Macia, <persName
                                    key="#Arimannus #childOf"><name ref="Godo/f. Rodulfi/de presbitero">Godo</name></persName> filius
                            <persName key="#parentOf"><name ref="Rodulfus/de presbitero">Rodulfi</name></persName>
                        de <rs key="#Priests">presbitero</rs>
                        <persName><name ref="Danihel">Daniele</name></persName>. Actum est hoc supra
                        ipsam terram. Anno dominice incarnationis millesimo centesimo vigesimo
                        sexto, tercio die exeunte mense iulii, inditione quarta. Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Albertus/de Casalealto">Albertus</name></persName> de
                        <placeName ref="#places/2963">Casalealto</placeName> interfui et subscripsi. Interfuerunt
                        ibi <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Aimerigus"
                            >Agimericus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Bulgarus/de Ingo">Bulgarus</name></persName> de <persName><name
                                ref="Ingo">Ingo</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"
                            ><name ref="Lanfrancus/de Desenzano">Lanfrancus</name></persName> de Descenzano, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Cafarus/de Melata">Cafarus</name></persName> de Melata, <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Hugo/Cupa/de Graula">Ugo Cupa</name></persName> de
                        Graula, <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Beatus"
                        >Beatus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"
                            ><name ref="Artusius/de Calcinato">Artusius</name></persName> de Calcinato, <persName key="#Witness"
                                ><name ref="Hubaldus/Vicedominus">Ubaldus
                            Vicedominus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Rodulfus">Rodulfus</name></persName> nepos eius, <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Winizo/de Casale">Winizo</name></persName> de Casale,
                        [.]aginaldusr de Septinenti. (SN) Ego <persName key="#Notary #Writer" ref="°people/3573">Bonus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> sacri palacii intetfui, rogatus <rs
                            key="#Writer">scripsi</rs>. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
